OL,3,CLittle evidence that employing
OL,4,Cphysician associates in NHS is safe `
OL,5,Cresearch
OL,7,FThere is little evidence that
OL,8,Femploying physician associates (PAs)
OL,9,Fin the NHS is safe or that they
OL,10,Fimprove patient care, a review from
OL,11,FOxford University has found.
OL,13,FExperts said studies relating the role
OL,14,Fof PAs and anaesthetic associates
OL,15,F(AAs) were severely lacking, despite
OL,16,Fmore than 3,500 people being employed
OL,17,Fin these roles in the health service.
