OL,5,Cresearch
OL,7,FWhile some research has suggested PAs
OL,8,Fcould support the work of hospital
OL,9,Fward teams and A&E when appropriately
OL,10,Fdeployed and supervised, "the number
OL,11,Fof individuals and settings studied
OL,12,Fwas small, and those findings should
OL,13,Fbe considered preliminary", the team
OL,14,Fsaid.
OL,16,FFurthermore, the researchers found
OL,17,Fsome NHS staff had concerns about the
OL,18,Fcompetence of PAs and AAs "to manage
OL,19,Fundifferentiated, clinically complex,
OL,20,For high dependency patients... or
OL,21,Fprescribe".
