OL,7,FPAs are graduates ` usually with a
OL,8,Fhealth or life sciences degree ` who
OL,9,Fhave undertaken two years of
OL,10,Fpostgraduate training.
OL,12,FAccording to the NHS, they should work
OL,13,Funder the supervision of a doctor and
OL,14,Fcan diagnose people, take medical
OL,15,Fhistories, perform physical
OL,16,Fexaminations, see patients with long-
OL,17,Fterm conditions, analyse test results
OL,18,Fand develop management plans.
