OL,3,CLittle evidence that employing
OL,4,Cphysician associates in NHS is safe `
OL,5,Cresearch
OL,7,FOnly one study, of four PAs, involved
OL,8,Fany assessment by a doctor of their
OL,9,Fclinical competence by direct
OL,10,Fobservation, and "no studies examined
OL,11,Fsafety incidents".
OL,13,FThe experts also found no evidence
OL,14,Fthat deploying PAs or AAs improves
OL,15,Fefficiency or saves money.
OL,17,FIn fact, as a senior doctor is needed
OL,18,Fto oversee and check the work of PAs
OL,19,Fand AAs, this model may be more
OL,20,Fexpensive than employing doctors, they
OL,21,Fsaid.
OL,26,@rD@ROUsD@QO]
